        "type": "message",
        "text": "Hey B2B pals :wave:\n\nAfter 3.5 years at hotjar, I started a 'giving back' plan to share the content lessons I learned over there.\nIn my first 'episode', I talked about Subject Matter Experts (SMEs) and their role in creating good content.\n\nIn my experience:\n- if you hire a subject matter expert to write basic stuff, that’s a waste of their time and expertise\n- if you hire a generalist to write about highly complex topics, the result is (mostly) going to be :hankey:\n- workaround: train someone to find and interview SMEs and use transcripts as a source, but accept that this will slow the process down\n\n:bulb:  *What's your experience here? How do you make it work?*",
